      "tender": {
        "id": "KNOWS001-DN501282-11650597",
        "title": "Sheltered Accommodation & Dispersed Alarm Service",
        "description": "Sheltered Accommodation\\r\r\n\\r\r\nTo provide support to Knowsley residents to enable them to live independently who are generally over the age of 55 years.  There is assistance from a scheme manager (warden) or support staff, 24-hour emergency response through an alarm system, majority have communal areas and social activities for residents.\\r\r\n\\r\r\nDispersed Alarm Service\\r\r\n\\r\r\nThe dispersed alarm service is a telecare monitoring system for residents living in their own homes in the community but it is not part of the sheltered accommodation service.  The service provides an emergency response should a resident activate the telecare monitoring alarm 24 hours a day to either Home Care Link or the providers own telecare monitoring provider.",
        "status": "complete",
        "classification": {
          "scheme": "CPV",
          "id": "85311000",
          "description": "Social work services with accommodation"
